    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>ABC announced that it will order a second season for a show once thought irretrievably dead: 'Making the Band.'' The network ordered 13 more episodes yesterday and may have it available for mid-season.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>ABC announced that it will order a second season for a show once thought irretrievably dead: 'Making the Band.'' The network ordered 13 more episodes yesterday and may have it available for mid-season.</p>
        <p>While it has never exploded in the ratings, the series, about the development of a boy band, has attracted something of a cult following. It also fits the genre of reality programming, which means it would not be affected by a strike of actors and writers.</p>
        <p>BILL CARTER</p>
        <p>TV NOTES</p>
      </block>
